A Lotus Formula One car raced by British driver Graham Hill is set to fetch up to £1million at auction.

The Lotus 49B Grand Prix car was also raced by fellow world champions Jim Clark, Jochen Rindt and Emerson Fittipaldi.

Designed by Lotus legend Colin Chapman and built in 1968, the iconic car is one of only a handful of 49s still in existence.

