It is the last Lotus to be sold from the collection of late British racer John Dawson-Damer.

Dawson-Damer tragically died when he crashed his 1969 Lotus 63 at the Goodwood Festival of Speed in 2000.

The car is expected to draw interest from collectors at the Bonhams’ sale at the same Goodwood festival in June.

James Knight, Bonhams group motoring director, said: 'By every standard, Colin Chapman’s Lotus 49 concept is an absolute landmark in Formula One design.

'It simply raised the bar for every rival manufacturer and its Cosworth-Ford V8 engine went on to win a record 155 world championship Grands Prix.

